<main class="page">
  <h1>About This Project</h1>
  <p>
    <strong>StopAmbulanceBalanceBills.org</strong> is a public-interest initiative focused on ending surprise
    balance billing for ground ambulance services in the United States.
  </p>

  <h2>Why this exists</h2>
  <p>
    People call 911 because they need help, not because they want to gamble with a multi-thousand dollar bill.
    Yet across the country, patients are being hit with huge ambulance charges they never agreed to and could
    never reasonably avoid.
  </p>

  <h2>What we&rsquo;re building</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Clear explanations of how ambulance billing works and why balance billing happens</li>
    <li>A collection of real-world stories from affected patients and families</li>
    <li>Policy ideas and model proposals for lawmakers and advocates</li>
    <li>Tools for contacting representatives and spreading awareness</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who maintains this</h2>
  <p>
    This project is maintained by <strong>Jonathan Kendall (onojk123)</strong>, as a small but focused effort to shine
    light on an overlooked piece of the U.S. healthcare system and to push for specific, actionable reforms.
  </p>

